::Shadow Wing::

She was starting to get worried about Lunarpine.  He had been gone a 
long time and had not checked in.  She knew he was out there 
somewhere working out his problems and frustrations.  She wanted to 
be a help to him and not a hinderance.  She remembered his gruff 
voice the last time she talked to him.  He didn't want to be 
disturbed while following his instincts.  She had her instintcs 
telling her something was wrong.  She wanted to go out and find him 
to make sure he was OK.  But then she thought she would be bothering 
him and he would be mad at her for interfering.  She sighed and went 
back inside the ark.  She walked around till she came to his 
quarters.  She looked at the empty room and wished he was here to 
tell her not to worry and that he was alright.  She walked back to 
the entrance of the ship and waited for him to return.
